    "dimensions": "145 cm x 195 cm",
    "location": "Galleria Nazionale d'Arte Antica, Rome, Italy",
    "description": "This visceral depiction of the biblical heroine Judith slaying the Assyrian general Holofernes is one of Caravaggio's most dramatic works. The scene captures the exact moment of decapitation, with Judith's expression caught between determination and revulsion. The stark chiaroscuro lighting intensifies the horror, isolating the three figures against an impenetrable black void.",
