  {
    "id": "caravaggio-calling-of-saint-matthew",
    "title": "The Calling of Saint Matthew",
    "artist": "Caravaggio",
    "year": 1600,
    "medium": "Oil on canvas",
    "dimensions": "322 cm x 340 cm",
    "location": "Contarelli Chapel, San Luigi dei Francesi, Rome, Italy",
    "description": "A masterpiece of Baroque drama, this monumental canvas depicts the moment Christ enters a dimly lit tax collector's office to call Matthew to his service. A shaft of divine light cuts diagonally across the composition, illuminating the startled group of men at the table. The juxtaposition of contemporary Renaissance dress with biblical narrative was revolutionary for its time.",
