    "dimensions": "169.5 cm x 216.5 cm",
    "location": "Mauritshuis, The Hague, Netherlands",
    "description": "This group portrait depicts Dr. Tulp demonstrating the musculature of the forearm to seven members of the Amsterdam Guild of Surgeons. Rembrandt arranges the observers in a pyramidal composition, their rapt faces illuminated against a dark background. The cadaver's pallid flesh contrasts starkly with the living warmth of the surgeons' faces, creating a meditation on mortality and knowledge.",
