    "location": "Museo del Prado, Madrid, Spain",
    "description": "Often called the greatest painting in Western art, Las Meninas depicts a complex scene in the Spanish royal court where Velazquez himself stands painting at a large canvas. The young Infanta Margarita is attended by her maids of honor, dwarfs, and a mastiff, while the King and Queen appear reflected in a mirror on the back wall. The painting is a profound meditation on the nature of representation, perception, and the relationship between artist and subject.",
